Overview

This document lists the public subIds for ADF Faces components. A SubId is used to access a DOM element within a component without having to worry about future changes to the internal DOM representation of the component.

To learn how to use SubIds in Selenium Automated Tests, please go to Oracle ADF Faces - Selenium Automation Examples

diagram

External SubId Internal Client SubId

link[index] link at the specific index of the link collection (mapped programmatically)
link[index]:stampId stamped component representing a custom start or end link connector for the link at the specific index of the link collection (mapped programmatically)
node[index] node at the specific index of the node collection (mapped programmatically)
node[index]#additionalLinks additional links button for a node at the specific index of the node collection (mapped programmatically)
node[index]#disclosure disclosure button for a node at the specific index of the node collection where the action (open or close) of the disclosure button is determined by the current state of the node (mapped programmatically)
node[index]#drill drill button for a node at the specific index of the node collection (mapped programmatically)
node[index]#isolate isolate button for a node at the specific index of the node collection (mapped programmatically)
node[index]#stacking stacking button for a node at the specific index of the node collection where the action (unstack or restack) of the stacking button is determined by the current state of the node (mapped programmatically)
node[index]:stampId stamped component in node at the specific index of the node collection (mapped programmatically)
restore restore button present after isolating on a node

Indexing Examples: 
1) click("rich=idDiagram#breadcrumbs[1]"); 

2) click("rich=idDiagram#node[0]"); click("rich=idDiagram#node[0]#drill"); 

3) click("rich=diagramId#node[0]"); click("rich=diagramId#node[0]#isolate"); 

4) click("rich=diagramId#node[0]"); click("rich=diagramId#node[0]#additionalLinks"); 

5) click("rich=diagramId#node[0]"); click("rich=diagramId#node[0]#stacking"); 

6) click("rich=diagramId#node[0]#disclosure"); 

7) click("rich=idDiagram#node[4]:outputText1"); 

8) callRichComponentFunctionChain("rich=idDiagram", new String[]{"getNode", "getColor"}, new Object[][]{{7},{}}); 

9) callRichComponentFunctionChain("rich=idDiagram", new String[]{"getNode", "getComponent", "getCardCount"}, new Object[][]{{7},{"panelCard1"},{}});
 
Click on the second entry in the breadcrumbs to navigate up the hierarchy. 

Click and then drill into the node at index 0 in the node collection. 

Click and then isolate on the node at index 0 in the node collection. 

Click and then show the incoming and outgoing links for the node at index 0 of the node collection. 

Click and unstack or restack the node at index 0 of the node collection. 

Click to disclose or undisclose the node at index 0 of the node collection. 

Click on the output text item with id outputText1 within the node at index 4 in the node collection. 

Get the color of the node at index 7 in the node collection. 

Get the card count for the panel card with id panelCard1 of the node at index 7 in the node collection.

External SubId Internal Client SubId

Verification APIs are listed below. Requires calling rich component ( e.g. AdfRichGraph.getTitle() ) apis. See Selenium Automation Examples using link at the top of this page for instructions on how to use Flash verification apis.
verification api: AdfGraphAxis.getTitle():String graph axis title
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getColor():String data marker color. Please note that the default graph colors are subject to change, so only test colors that have been explicitly overridden.
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getText():String data marker text / slice label
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getTooltip():String data marker tooltip
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getValueActual():Number data marker actual value. Only valid for funnel graph markers.
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getValueClose():Number data marker close value. Only valid for stock graph markers.
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getValueHigh():Number data marker high value. Only valid for stock graph markers.
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getValueLow():Number data marker low value. Only valid for stock graph markers.
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getValueOpen():Number data marker open value. Only valid for stock graph markers.
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getValueTarget():Number data marker target value. Only valid for funnel graph markers.
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getValueX():Number data marker X axis value
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getValueY():Number data marker Y1/Y2 axis value
verification api: AdfGraphDataMarker.getValueZ():Number data marker Z value. Only used to represent size of a data marker on a bubble graph
verification api: AdfGraphLegend.getTitle():String legend title
verification api: AdfRichGraph.getDataMarker(seriesIndex:Number,groupIndex:Number):AdfGraphDataMarker data marker for a specific series / group.
verification api: AdfRichGraph.getGroupCount():Number number of groups in the data model
verification api: AdfRichGraph.getLegend():AdfGraphLegend legend
verification api: AdfRichGraph.getO1Axis():AdfGraphAxis O1 axis
verification api: AdfRichGraph.getSeriesCount():Number number of series in the data model
verification api: AdfRichGraph.getTitle():String title.
verification api: AdfRichGraph.getX1Axis():AdfGraphAxis X1 axis
verification api: AdfRichGraph.getY1Axis():AdfGraphAxis Y1 axis
verification api: AdfRichGraph.getY2Axis():AdfGraphAxis Y2 axis
